Interface Incrementable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BarReadout, BufferReadout, DialReadout, LevelReadout

    public interface Incrementable
    Defines the functionality of a class that can be incremented and decremented. The exact interpretation of incrementing and decrementing is left to the implementing subclass.
    Author:
    Mark Sabini
